<plot>In this Traveltalk look at Canada's province of Nova Scotia, we visit several coastal communities. The first stop is Lunenberg, where deep sea fishing and shipbuilding are the main industries. Other stops include Blue Rocks, where lobstering is an important source of income, and Peggy's Cove, known for its artist community.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?411397</url></doc>
